e H	riangleleft G.$  Show that $H\cap Z(G)
e\{e\}.$ Consider the commutator subgroup $G'<G.$ For any $N	riangleleft G$ with $G/N$ Abelian, we have that $G'\subset N.$ Thus since $Z(G)$ is a normal subgroup of $G$ and the quotient group is Abelian by assumption, $G'\subset Z(G).$ Now let $g\in G$ and $h\in H$. Then  $$ghg^{-1}h^{-1} = (ghg^{-1})h^{-1}\in H\cap G'.$$ Now if $ghg^{-1}h^{-1}
e e$ for some $g,h,$ then we're done. But if $ghg^{-1}h^{-1} = e$ for all $g\in G,\; h\in H$, then this implies $H\subset Z(G)$.

